text.tspan: In total 14,933 ARGs were collected from the CARD,
ARDB, and UNIPROT databases. The resulting database,
the genes belong to the Beta lactamase class (5136), followed
accounting for the major antibiotic resistance classes in deepARG-DB
The deepARG models perform particularly well
for antibiotic resistance categories containing a large number of ARGs,
such as beta lactamases, bacitracin, and MLS, but not as well for categories
with a small number of ARGs, such as triclosan and aminocoumarin.
Overall, it outperforms the predictions achieved using a simple best hit approach.
